I've estimated that I'm 15 years old,
although I have no way of knowing.

7
00:00:35,993 --> 00:00:38,912
Changnesia is a fascinating
and extremely rare disease...

8
00:00:39,205 --> 00:00:41,665
on the forefront of
the psychological landscape.

9
00:00:41,958 --> 00:00:43,834
Compared with
your garden-variety amnesia...

10
00:00:44,126 --> 00:00:46,628
Changnesia is immeasurably
more complex.

11
00:00:48,673 --> 00:00:51,425
Its varied and seemingly
random symptoms...

12
00:00:51,717 --> 00:00:54,886
its resistance to both traditional
and new age medicine.

13
00:00:55,179 --> 00:00:58,891
Why Changnesia affects the memory
but not the ability to make forced puns.

14
00:00:59,433 --> 00:01:02,144
These are all things we can study
now that someone has it.

15
00:01:02,853 --> 00:01:06,147
I first met Chang when I hired him
as a Spanish teacher at Greendale.

16
00:01:06,440 --> 00:01:10,652
Then he became a disgraced student,
a psychopathic music major...

17
00:01:10,945 --> 00:01:13,489
a homeless vent dweller,
security guard, keytarist...

18
00:01:13,781 --> 00:01:16,241
power-hungry warlord,
and now Kevin.

19
00:01:16,534 --> 00:01:18,827
It's sad to see him like this.
Well, it's mixed.

20
00:01:19,120 --> 00:01:20,412
He was pretty terrible before.

21
00:01:20,705 --> 00:01:23,290
I'm developing a theory
which some find controversial.

22
00:01:23,583 --> 00:01:25,626
Perhaps Chang actually
used to be Kevin...

23
00:01:25,918 --> 00:01:27,461
went crazy, and became Chang.

24
00:01:27,753 --> 00:01:31,173
And then at some point,
Chang hit his head, went un-crazy...

25
00:01:31,465 --> 00:01:34,593
thereby reverting back
to regular old Kevin again.

26
00:01:34,885 --> 00:01:36,761
That makes no sense.

27
00:01:37,054 --> 00:01:40,474
Science tells us hitting his head
would only cure him...

28
00:01:40,766 --> 00:01:43,018
if hitting his head
was the original cause.

29
00:01:43,311 --> 00:01:44,770
I told you it was controversial.

30
00:01:45,062 --> 00:01:46,938
Here at Greendale,
we accept all students...

31
00:01:47,231 --> 00:01:49,775
whoever they may be
or have forgotten they were.

32
00:01:50,067 --> 00:01:53,862
But assisting in Kevin's recovery has
put a financial strain on the school.

33
00:01:54,155 --> 00:01:55,614
That's why we are appealing...

34
00:01:55,906 --> 00:01:59,284
to the MacGuffin Neurological
Institute for this $40,000 grant...

35
00:01:59,577 --> 00:02:02,580
so we can continue to fight
this terrible disease...

36
00:02:02,872 --> 00:02:06,292
and hopefully, one day,
pay for this documentary.

37
00:02:07,209 --> 00:02:08,919
How was that, Abed? It's too beggy?

38
00:02:09,211 --> 00:02:10,211
No, that was great.

39
00:02:10,421 --> 00:02:12,756
But I could use a new camera
with a smoother zoom.

40
00:02:13,049 --> 00:02:15,217
Okay. Just be sure
to get my good side.

41
00:02:15,509 --> 00:02:17,219
This documentary needs
to be convincing.

42
00:02:17,511 --> 00:02:20,889
This needs to be the Hoop Dreams
of things people care about.

43
00:02:21,182 --> 00:02:22,600
We rolling?

44
00:02:24,185 --> 00:02:28,230
Dean wants propaganda but I intend to
explore all sides of this serious issue...

45
00:02:28,522 --> 00:02:30,982
including those who don't think
it's a serious issue.

46
00:02:31,484 --> 00:02:33,152
- Hey, Jeff.
- What are you doing?

47
00:02:33,444 --> 00:02:36,238
- A documentary on Changnesia.
- You gotta be ♪♪♪♪♪♪♪ kidding me.

48
00:02:36,530 --> 00:02:39,324
Got it. Beautiful.
All right, let's get one more for safety.

49
00:02:39,617 --> 00:02:41,702
Jeff, back to one. Jeff?

50
00:02:43,788 --> 00:02:45,623
♪ Give me some more
